<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[119,1140,1233,1380]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
Notes. The identification raised some doubts because other representatives of the genus – 
<emphasis box="[119,362,1264,1288]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Rhinoglena fertoeensis</emphasis>
(Varga, 1929) and recently described 
<emphasis box="[765,909,1264,1288]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Rh. kutikovae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De Smet" box="[915,1072,1264,1288]" firstAuthor="De Smet" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" pagination="595 - 603" refId="ref8927" refString="DE SMET W. H. &amp; GIBSON J. A. E. 2008. Rhinoglena kutikovae n. sp. (Rotifera: Monogononta: Epiphanidae) from the Bunger Hills, East Antarctica: a probable relict species that survived quaternary glaciations. Polar Biology 31: 595 - 603. DOI: http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00300 - 007 - 0393 - 9" type="journal article" year="2008">De Smet, 2008</bibRefCitation>
– also inhabit East 
<taxonomicName authority=", Bunger Hills" authorityName="Bunger Hills" box="[257,523,1295,1319]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Philodinidae" genus="Philodina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bdelloidea" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="antarctica">Antarctica, Bunger Hills</taxonomicName>
oasis (
<bibRefCitation author="KUTIKOVA L. A." box="[601,765,1295,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" pagination="45 - 46" refId="ref10058" refString="KUTIKOVA L. A. 1958. A new rotifer from the Antarctic. Soviet Antarctic Expedition Information Bulletin 2: 45 - 46. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="1958">Kutikova 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="KUTIKOVA L. A." box="[781,834,1295,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" pagination="87 - 99" refId="ref10156" refString="KUTIKOVA L. A. 1991. Rotifers of the inland waters of East Antarctica. Soviet Antarctic Expedition Information Bulletin 116: 87 - 99. [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1991">1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="De Smet &amp; Gibson" box="[850,1128,1295,1319]" firstAuthor="De Smet" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" pagination="595 - 603" refId="ref8927" refString="DE SMET W. H. &amp; GIBSON J. A. E. 2008. Rhinoglena kutikovae n. sp. (Rotifera: Monogononta: Epiphanidae) from the Bunger Hills, East Antarctica: a probable relict species that survived quaternary glaciations. Polar Biology 31: 595 - 603. DOI: http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00300 - 007 - 0393 - 9" type="journal article" year="2008">De Smet &amp; Gibson 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Especially, we did not observe trophi of the collected 
<emphasis box="[693,816,1325,1349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Rhinoglena</emphasis>
individuals; hence, we should determine the species as ‘ 
<emphasis box="[392,516,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Rhinoglena</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[557,647,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">frontalis</emphasis>
’.
</paragraph>
